crepererum commented on a change in pull request #1846: ARROW-2408: [Rust] Ability to get `&mut [T]` from `Buffer<T>`
URL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/1846#discussion_r179813579



 ##########
 File path: rust/src/builder.rs
 ##########
 @@ -48,6 +47,18 @@ impl<T> Builder<T> {
         }
     }

+    /// Get the internal byte-aligned memory buffer as a mutable slice
+    pub fn slice_mut(&self, start: usize, end: usize) -> &mut [T] {
+        unsafe {
+            slice::from_raw_parts_mut(self.data.offset(start as isize), (end - start) as usize)
+        }
+    }
+
+    /// Override the length
+    pub fn set_len(&mut self, len: usize) {

 Review comment:
   So this function should semantically be marked as `unsafe`, since the user could set this to whatever value (even higher then the actual capacity).

